6 An Act relating to contractors; amending 59 O.S.
2021, Section 1158, which relates to installation of
7 individual sewage disposal systems; decreasing number
of installations for certain certification; updating
8 statutory language; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1158, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 1158. A. On and after July 1, 2002, any person, before
15 engaging in the installation of individual sewage disposal systems,
16 shall first obtain certification from the Department of
17 Environmental Quality under such rules as may be promulgated by the
18 Environmental Quality Board. The provisions of this subsection
19 shall only apply to persons who install more than ten one individual
20 sewage disposal systems system per calendar year. As used in this
21 section, “individual sewage disposal systems system” means a sewage
22 disposal system that serves an individual residence or duplex and is
23 not available for use by the general public.
24
